<p>Typically, the best way to have a concept seen to start with is to have a title that indicates something the audience has never seen before (that grabs initial attention), a thread summary that isn't too long (otherwise reviewers may feel like the author is prone to ramble and include a bunch of unnecessary fluff text), and a succinct, well-written concept summary.</p>
